Foreign Companies Eye Greek Gaming Licences, Naftemporiki Says

-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 
2011-10-18T07:43:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/foreign-companies-eye-greek-gaming-licences-naftemporiki-says.html
France’s Francaise des Jeux,
 Scientific Games Corp. (SGMS)  of the U.S. and Italy’s  Lottomatica SpA (LTO) 
are among possible bidders for licences to operate  Greece ’s
state lottery and Xisto lottery game,  Naftemporiki  said.  Greece’s Intralot SA is also looking to bid for the
licences while  Opap SA (OPAP)  has already expressed an intention to do
so, the Athens-based newspaper said, without citing anyone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell at 
